com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.swing

Class PSvgIcon

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.googlecode.kevinarpe.papaya.swing.PSvgIcon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Accessible, Icon

    @NotFullyTested
@Beta
public class PSvgIcon
extends Object
implements Icon, Accessible
    A small fixed size picture, typically used to decorate components, rendered from SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics) data.

    This class is highly experimental and many SVG icons available in open source icon themes do not render correctly with this class and throw exceptions.

    Author:
    Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
    See Also:
    Icon

    • Constructor Detail

      • PSvgIcon

        public PSvgIcon(org.apache.batik.transcoder.TranscoderInput input,
        int width,
        int height)
         throws org.apache.batik.transcoder.TranscoderException
        Constructs an Icon from SVG data.
        Parameters:
        input - source for SVG data. If unfamiliar with this parameter type, it can accept a wide variety of input sources: Document, InputStream, Reader, URI, and XMLReader.
        width - integral number of pixels on X-axis to render the BufferedImage
        height - integral number of pixels on Y-axis to render the BufferedImage
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if input is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if width or height is not positive
        org.apache.batik.transcoder.TranscoderException - if SVG fails to render as an BufferedImage
